      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 766: mallopt(M_ARENA_MAX, 2) is called after Manager::init has already performed substantial initialization and possibly after other threads/allocations have created arenas. Existing arenas are not removed by lowering the cap, so this may fail to bound RSS in the cases this patch is intended to fix. Move this as early as possible in process startup, before thread pools or allocation-heavy subsystems are initialized, and check/log failure so deployments can tell whether the setting was applied.\n\n```suggestion\n    if (mallopt(M_ARENA_MAX, 2) \u003d\u003d 0)\n        JAMI_WARN(\"Failed to set glibc malloc arena limit\");\n```",
