      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 1778: Calling malloc_trim(0) directly from the daemon io_context can block the event loop while glibc walks arenas and acquires allocator locks. Since this io_context also drives asynchronous daemon work, a trim after call teardown can introduce latency or stalls in unrelated signaling/timer operations. Run the trim on a background/thread-pool context and only use the io_context for debouncing.\n\n```suggestion\n        timer-\u003easync_wait([](const asio::error_code\u0026 ec) {\n            if (!ec) {\n                dht::ThreadPool::io().run([] { malloc_trim(0); });\n            }\n        });\n```",
